cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper deals with clustering time series data generated by multiple deterministic linear dynamical systems. This falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a likely category as it deals with clustering and analyzing data. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a new distance measure for clustering time series data. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with identifying underlying dynamics of input/output signals. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed distance measure. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with identifying patterns in time series data.
